1. Added the ability to start the script logged in. 2. If it can't find the targets it will attempt to teleport to ::range 3. Moved some things around abit 4. Can now choose wait time between clicks. 4. Added DTMS: Now finds the target via DTM. Now finds 'Close Window' via DTM, ALOT more accurate!
[s]This is the first and beta version of one of my first scripts. It trains your range by clicking on the targets a specified amount of times.[/s] This is now pretty much finished. I exercised new things such as bitmaps and DTMS and other things.
[s] First it requires for you to be logged out located near the targets. This will be changed later. It will then log you in and begin clicking the targets.[/s] Updated! Now you have the choice to be either logged in or out! And now if it can't find the targets it will type ::range! (Teleports to targets on [b]MOST[/b] servers.) It will then begin clicking a specified amount of times on the targets.
Alright here it is.
{Note that I made this for learning purposes}
